WorkItem.Description:
I use enums in my project and I am getting bugged by the fact that enums are presented as numbers. Consider this:

```
enum Foo {
 ONE,
 TWO
};

var value = Foo.ONE;
if (value) {
 // Do someting
}
```

The fact that Foo.ONE is actually 0 in the code makes this check fail although I have assigned a value. 

I think one fix would be to just start the enum values with "1" instead of "0".
